es / My passions in their tomb are soundly sleeping -- tCreyó que era eterno tu reino en el alma / He thought thy kingdom was eternal in the soul -- tYa siente que te extingues en su seno / He feels already that the vital flame -- tNo subas tan alto, pensamiento loco / Soar not so high, mad thought! -- tEn su cárcel de espinos y rosas / In their prison of hawthorns and roses -- tYa no mana la fuente, se agotó el manantial / Now the brook is dry, the spring has ceased to flow -- tCenicientas las aguas, los desnudos / Ashen are the waters, ashen the hills -- tEra la última noche / It was the final night -- t¡Volved! / Return ! -- tCamino blanco, viejo camino / White road, old road, stony, rough, and narrow -- tAun parece que asoman tras del Miranda altivo / I think behind Miranda's peak May's dawns are still appearing -- tCerrado capullo de pálidas tintas / Primly shut rosebud pallidly tinted -- tEn sus ojos rasgados y azules / In her eyes so blue and wide -- tFué cielo de su espíritu, fué sueño de sus sueños / Heaven to his spirit was she, and dream of his dreams -- tTe amo... ¿por qué me odias? / "I love you. Why do you hate me?" -- tNada me importa, blanca o negra mariposa / I do not care, little moths, if you be black or white -- tMuda la luna y como siempre pálida / Silent the moon and, as her wont is, pale -- tNos dicen que se adoran la aurora y el crepúsculo / Say not that dawn and eventide are lovers! -- tUna sombra tristísima, indefinible y vaga / Always before me a somber shadow moves, shapeless -- t¡Aturde la confusa gritería / What a confused and stupefying shout -- tDe la vida entre el múltiple conjunto de los seres / Seek not the image of eternal Beauty -- tQuisiera, hermosa mía / "I wish, dear heart, sweet mistress of my will -- tA la sombra te sientas de las desnudas rocas / "You sit sometimes, my dear, in a bare boulder's shade" -- tEn los ecos del órgano, o en el rumor del viento / In organ-echoes or in planet's gleaming -- tSanta Escolástica / Saint Scholastica -- tDicen que no hablan las plantas, ni las fuentes, ni los pájaros / They say that a plant has no speech, nor a brook, nor a bird -- tCada vez que recuerda tanto oprobio / Each time that he remembers his disgrace -- tRecuerda el trinar del ave / The sweet wild notes of a singing bird -- tMientras el hielo las cubre / While winter over my garden -- tPensaban que estaba ocioso / They thought that he was idle -- tBrillaban en la altura cual moribundas chispas / The pallid stars, like dying sparks, were faint -- tSon los corazones de algunas criaturas / Beings there are whose well-worn hearts are like -- tAl oír las canciones / Whenever I hear the songs -- tVosotros que del cielo que forjasteis / O ye who live enamored of the heaven -- tA la Luna / To the Moon -- tLa palabra y la idea... hay un abismo / Word and ideal What an abyss there is -- tLas Campanas / The Bells -- tAnsia que ardiente crece / Passion new-burning -- tA las rubias envidias / Just because you are dark, Marie -- tDe este mundo en la comedia / Wrapped in the selfsame veil, there go -- tTriste loco de atar, el que ama menos / He of less love calls him of greater love -- tJusticia de los hombres, yo te busco / Justice I cannot ever find in men -- tSintiéndose acabar con el estío / The ailing woman felt her forces ebb -- tUna cuerda tirante guarda mi seno / My bosom holds a single tight-drawn string -- tDesde los cuatro puntos cardinales / Despite her wrinkles our Mother Earth is young -- tAun otra amarga gota en el mar sin orillas / One more sour drop goes to the shoreless sea -- tEn incesante encarnizada lucha / In fierce, incessant struggle -- tGlorias hay que deslumhran, cual deslumhra / Glories there are which dazzle like a flash -- t¡Oh gloria! deidad vana cual todas las deidades / O Fame! vain deity, as all deities are vain -- tTiemblan las hojas, y mi alma tiembla / Tremble the dying leaves, and my soul trembles! -- tNo va solo el que llora / My tears, I hope, will never cease to flow -- t«¡La copa es de oro fino / The cup is of fine gold -- tYo no he nacido para odiar, sin duda / I know I was not born to hate -- tMás rápidos que el rayo / Swifter than lightning -- tHora tras hora, día tras día / Hour follows hour, day follows day -- tTan sólo dudas y terrores siento / Nothing but doubt and terror are my fate -- tNOTES TO THE PREFACE -- tNOTES TO THE POEMS -- tBIBLIOGRAPHY0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 21. Jun 2021) 7aNON-CLASSIFIABLE.2bisacsh1 aMorley, S. Griswold.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Package Archive Pre-2000z978311063534840uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052034511940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520345119423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780520345119.jpg  a978-3-11-063534-8  University of California Press Package Archive Pre-2000  aGBV-deGruyter-alles